<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="allosteric_regulation">Allosteric Regulation</a> - Allosteric regulation happens when a <a href="#conformation">conformational change</a> (the allosteric part) affects the function of a <a href="#protein">protein</a> or <a href="#enzyme">enzyme</a>. For example, a small <a href="#molecule">molecule</a> may bind a <a href="#transcription_factor_tf">transcription factor</a> and cause a <a href="#conformation">conformational change</a> that removes the <a href="#transcription_factor_tf">TF</a>'s ability to bind <a href="#dna_desoxyribonucleic_acid">DNA</a>, rendering it inactive.